d nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#333333>(1/12/02 12:28:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  what i think needs to be done to fix mages...discuss.</span><hr size=1> i wanted to get an active class balance thread going.<br>
<br>
i'll start by posting some ideas i have been brainstorming lately which i recently submitted via a comment to the dev corner @ verants official boards.<br>
 <br>
feel free to contribute <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  helpful</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> constructive criticizem of my ideas, or post original ideas of your own.<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
[*]before any actual balance work is done, verant needs to make an official statement citing where they feel every class should perform offensively in long term damage (or synonomously &quot;over all&quot;) against the warrior, just like they did for melee classes earlier in the year.<br>
<br>
this seed should be formed based on 3 important factors:<br>
-the speed in which some classes do damage...<br>
-the longevity with which some classes do damage... <br>
-the amount of support some classes have, and how important those supportive roles are. things such as damage absorbtion (tanking), pulling, sow, heals, ports, stuns, mez, bash (to interupt casting)... all that stuff should be judged on a case by case basis, and assigned a worth value. <br>
for example, <br>
-the less situational an ability (tanking vs pick locks), the higher the worth value. <br>
-the less potent an ability (air pet stuns vs cleric stuns), the lower its worth value. <br>
-if the ability is readily available on gear accessable to non-native classes, the worth value will drop, and the degree of availability will dictate by how much it will drop. <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  for example, eb might be considered worth extremely few support points, since it is readily available to non-native classes as well as highly situational.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
the higher your net supportive value, to counter balance the lower your net offensive value, and vise versa.<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BALANCING CASTING</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
1.01 enter caster focus items. make the word &quot;focus&quot; synonomous with &quot;caster weapon&quot;.<br>
<br>
[*]1.02 make it impossible for a caster to cast an offensive spell w/o a focus equiped in their primary slot. when you attempt, you receive a message: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;you weild no focus through which to channel mental energy!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. this step is very important: it makes casters dependant upon gear, like melees.<br>
supportive spells, however, may still be cast without focuses. the entire point of the introduction of focuses is to allow scalling for offensive spells, therefore, supportive and utility spells should remain the same.<br>
<br>
[*]1.03 focuses which make supportive spells more efficient to cast should also be available, however they will not be as prevelant or manditory.<br>
<br>
[*]1.04 implement a new tag titled &quot;focus&quot; to indicate which items are focuses, and which are not. not all caster primary &amp; 2/h equipable items will be focuses. <br>
<br>
[*]1.05 make focuses rarer for primarily supportive classes to obtain. this is also important: it clearly etches class roles in the sand, and adds a respectability to the job of an offensive caster (it always irks me as terribly unbalanced that any time an enchanter wants, they can nuke pretty darn well...)<br>
<br>
[*]1.06 make focuses have different values, depending on which class is equiping/looking at them. (i.e. a nec/wiz/mag/enc focus would weild the best stats for the wiz, worse for the mage, worse still for the necro, and the worst for the enchanter.)<br>
<br>
[*]1.07 focuses may have the following attributes: <br>
-mana cost<br>
-spell impact<br>
[the following values will typically be zero, except on mid-high end (L30+ zones) focuses.]<br>
-cast time<br>
-fizzle rate<br>
-resistance chance<br>
[the following will typically be zero, except on high end (L50+ zones) focuses.]<br>
-reduction to hate<br>
<br>
these properties will be quantified by percentage values.<br>
for aesthetical purposes, we'll use a 1-20 scale where every number equals 5%.<br>
the scale can go into negative numbers, allowing greater flexibility. <br>
last, every offensive spell will be &quot;seeded&quot; using the current stats as a base model to apply values against.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  example 1:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->lets assume you're a L49 mage. in your primary hand, you hold a well rounded upper mid-game focus. it has the following stats: <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  mana cost factor of 2<br>
impact factor of 4<br>
cast factor of 2</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
you cast lava bolt.<br>
base stats, this spell costs 300 mana, does 810 damage, with a cast time of 7 seconds. <br>
<br>
focused, this spell costs 270 mana, does 972 damage, with a cast time of 6.3 seconds. (mana/dmg ratio of 3.4... <br>
an increase of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  .7</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and an efficiency boost of about <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  26%</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  example 2:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->lets assume you hold a different focus -- this one is more of a high end focus, unlike the first. it differs from the first one, in it is designed to mold your spell to do substantially quicker, smaller bursts, yet very efficiently:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  mana factor of 10<br>
impact factor of -5<br>
cast factor of 4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
casting lava bolt:<br>
cost 150 mana, does 608 damage, cast time 5.6. (mana/damage ratio of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->,... an increase of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  1.3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and an efficiency boost of about <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  47%</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.)<br>
<br>
as for the other properties, fizzle, resist, and hate mods, the higher the percentage the less chance to fizzle/resist of course. (i.e. a focus with a resist factor of 5 would mean a 25% reduction to chance of resisting. this would mean that of every 4 resists you would get unfocused, you will only get 3 resists forcused.)<br>
<br>
[*]1.08 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  the bonuses on focus items will only be effective while grouped.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for balance when soloing, you will cast with only &quot;base&quot; efficiency. this step is also crucial to making casters more efficient -- change the way spells work inside and outside of groups.<br>
<br>
[*]1.09 include an &quot;others spell damage&quot; filter in the new gui, with the default being on. a good chunk of the caster imbalance problem is perception based (exadurated). doing this will help &quot;debrainwash&quot; the player base.<br>
<br>
[*]1.10 make mana regen items as common as melee hp regen items. there is no reason that i can see which 17 hp/tic items fall from the sky, allowing melees to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  solo</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with very little down time, yet a ft2 item, or even a stackable 5 mana per tic regen item should be viewed as uber and made no drop <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
[*]1.11 spells should be made to draw less hate than they currently do. there is no logical reason i can see, why when a spell is resisted it draws just as much hate as if it werent resisted.<br>
<br>
[*]1.12 remove researching and dropped spells from the game. casters should be balanced around gear from now on, and spells will be treated like melee discs/abilities/damage tables, meaning granted with level. spells will be awarded by your guild master at the appropriate level, free of charge.<br>
<br>
[*]1.13 resist rates should be cut, esspecially for lower level casters , and for higher level casters vs some uber mobs. many feel they are currently too high.<br>
<br>
[*]1.14 newbie caster's daggers should now have a focus tag on them (since otherwise they wouldnt be able to cast). the focus will be statless, and function only till level 20.<br>
after level 20, the caster must get out in the world and hunt down a real focus weapon, just like melees do              <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
it should be noted that focuses for newbies will be available earlier than that, but i figured it is only fair to allow a bit of a &quot;buffer zone&quot; for the new player.<br>
<br>
[*]1.15 fix the multi-caster dot stacking issue. this is will do alot to make some casters more efficient to have around. (i.e. 1st necro casts splurt, 2nd necro cannot.)<br>
<br>
[*]1.16 decrease the resist rates on rains. they are already limited in being ae, there is no reason for the resists to be so high.<br>
<br>
[*]1.17 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  impose a minimum nuke amount.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a nuke should not be able to land for less than 33% of total damage. it makes no sense that i can see, that backstabs have a minimum damage limit and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  not nukes</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> which are resource-based.<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BALANCING PETS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
2.01 implement a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  wealth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of various pet focus items, some which stack with other focuses, some which dont, all of various effects and potency. this is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  the golden ticket</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to fixing and scaling pet casters. focusing a pet should and must be viewed like equiping a melee.<br>
<br>
the following focuses will be introduced. all stack w/ each other as well as existing focuses, except the class unique bracelet series -- it (mostly) doesnt stack with earlier forms of itself. to receive the benefits, simply equip them before summoning your pet: <br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  gloves</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give a strength/attack boost. there will be lots of these gloves at all stages of the game (yes even the high end/raiding game), and they will be where the majority of your pets attack rating comes from. the best gloves, of course, will be only available to mage pets.<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  necklaces</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give your pet bonuses to its spell damage and/or reduces its likeliness to be resisted.<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  bps</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give your pet an ac/agi boost. there will be lots of these bps at all stages of the game, and they will be where the majority of your pets ac comes from. <br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  arms</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give a hp boost. again, they will be found at every stage of the game allowing pets to properly scale.<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  range slot items</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give your pet a signifigant boost in a specific resistance. if you summon a water pet while wearing the fire resistance focus for example, your pet will be completely imune to poison, and practically imune to fire.<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  belts</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which give your pet haste.<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  special ability jewelry</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which will grant your pet extra abilities (i.e. an earring which makes your pet fearless for an example).<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  bracelets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, unique to each major pet caster (mages bracelets being the best). these bracelets will be made in 4 installments available at all stages of the game. they will stack will all focus items, but not with themselves. the last installment will stack with 1 of the previous installments, but no more than that. the last installment will be for &quot;uber&quot; raiding players only. the bracelet will grant your pet: <br>
-more damage to pet spells, <br>
-haste, <br>
-ac,<br>
-attack <br>
-level(s),<br>
-resistances<br>
-make your pet spells less resistable<br>
-increase the duration of utility spells<br>
and so on.<br>
<br>
furthermore, every mage pet type will react differently to pet focus items, so as to keep the uniquness of each element in tact.<br>
<br>
[*]2.02 to allow for seemless scaling, nerf unfocused pets so they are similar to a melee fighting naked. this point, as well as point 2.01 will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  only apply to major pet casters</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (mage, nec, bst). this will help bring a greater margin of superiority between our pets, then say a shaman or an enchanters pet.<br>
<br>
[*]2.03 make the burnout series and valiant companion undispellable (and similar pet buffs of other casters).<br>
<br>
[*]2.04 remove/higher the pet haste cap.<br>
<br>
[*]2.05 in the new gui, do away with random generated pet names.<br>
change mage pets to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  character's elemental</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, for example. they are sloppy, and subconsciously i feel they make people uneasy around pets.<br>
<br>
[*]2.06 in the new gui, include a section for pet health bars.<br>
<br>
[*]2.07 make pets indifferent to everything.<br>
<br>
[*]2.08 make /pet hold a general skill. this and the above point will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  completely and totally eliminate any pet-related pathing problems</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
[*]2.09 introduce post-epic pets in raid-level zones (st, ntov, ect), which are conjured via items.<br>
<br>
[*]2.10 make the current epic pet more accessable to mid 50s mages like the rogue, wizard and monk epics (all which substantially increase dmg output for all 3 classes -- even the wizard epic if used properly).<br>
<br>
[*]2.11 newbie major pet casters (mag, nec, bst) will be given &quot;pet focus gloves&quot;, &quot;pet focus arms&quot;, and &quot;pet focus bp&quot;, in similar fashion to how the newbie warrior starts with a tunic and a training short sword.<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  FIXING THE TWINKING EPIDEMIC</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
3.01 this is really easy. simply, impose a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  skill limit</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on all items.<br>
when a level 10 warrior trys to equip a lammy, he wont be able to, and will receive the following message:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;you must have at least 190 skill in 1hs to weild this weapon.&quot;<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
when a level 10 wizard try to equip a new focus from sebilis:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;you must have at least 190 skill in evocation to utilize this focus.&quot;<br>
</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
and when a level 10 mage tries to equip the 3rd class specific bracelet:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;you must have at least 190 skill in conjuration to utilize this pet focus.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
i think you get where im going with this                  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
armor will work on defense caps.<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BOOSTING END GAME CASTERS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
4.01 as you may be aware, of all the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  primarily offensive</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> classes (rogues, wizards, monks, mages), mages have the greatest problems in the high end game. (by &quot;end game&quot;, i am refering to encounters vs level 55+ creatures).<br>
<br>
many have logged battles, and found mages were on average capable of only <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  bardic damage output</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> during such events. <br>
the commonly accepted theory, is this extremely low damage output is caused by the fact 60% of a mages damage output is in his/her pet -- but the nature of pets is such that their attack rating and level does not permit them to be effective vs very high level mobs.<br>
<br>
this is very much a problem for us, since the mage doesnt bring nearly as much support to a situation to warrent bardic offense. a mage brings both 3rd rate offense, as well as 3rd rate support during such encounters, making them not nearly as efficient as almost every other class. most will agree, that the plight of the end game magician is in dire need of attention.<br>
<br>
however, if some of these key points were to make it in the game (focus items for pets and casting, as well as making pets indifferent, and making pet hold a general skill), this problem would be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  resolved</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
for example, an &quot;end game&quot; mage could go with his/her guild to st or ntov, pick up pet focus items and scale their pets accordingly to meet challenges they will face, just as rogues and monks do.<br>
<br>
allowing pets to scale up via gear to meet challenges the &quot;end game&quot; pet master is expected to meet, is no more unbalancing than melee equiping themselves to meet such challenges. in fact, most mages/nec/bsts would agree: it is very much a needed step.<br>
<br>
it wouldnt trivialize the game and &quot;less difficult&quot; challenges <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  in any way moreso</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than well equiped melees do.<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  MAGE SPELLS/ABILITIES</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
5.01 the magician spell &quot;summon focus&quot; will be introduced, but only after real focuses flood the game, making it common knowledge a casters damage is suffering unless he strives to get the best focuses available (like melee weapons). the summon focus will be used mainly for crs (like summoned weapons) and will allow for worse than base damage output.<br>
<br>
5.02 increase the length of higher level ds's, so they become more mana efficient. with the prevelance of 70% slows, this is a necessary change.<br>
<br>
5.03 change all mage nukes to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
5.04 change the new luclin nuke so that it is 1300 dmg/400 mana.<br>
<br>
5.05 introduce new mage nukes at level 29, and level 39.<br>
<br>
5.06 make our dot line more mana efficient. there is almost no reason to use these spells over nukes since the ratio is about the same. in fact, they are less efficient when you consider dots may not work to full effect.<br>
<br>
5.07 introduce a series of summoned weapons, designed to add a proc to our pet. (upgrades to sword of runes)<br>
<br>
5.08 add more summoned creatures to the game (not really spell related but in the same vein).<br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BALANCING PVP</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
6.01 to cut back on griefing, make people exempt from pvp for 3 minutes after engaging an npc. this will help stop people from killing others who are low on health after fighting an npc.<br>
now, i know what youre thinking -- exploiters paradise. <br>
ive thought of a pre-emptive measure for potential exploits; make it so you wave your right to the &quot;3 minute rule&quot; if you partook in pvp within the past 5 minutes. (i.e. you cant just run up and whack a fire beetle if things are going bad)<br>
<br>
[*]6.02 to cut back on griefing, make people exempt from engaging in pvp after death for 10 minutes. <br>
no more corpse camping.<br>
<br>
[*]6.03 party members should no longer be hit by &quot;friendly fire&quot;<br>
<br>
[*]6.04 change the way resists and melee damage work in pvp. its not fair that casters are subjected to a 66% rule, but there is no penalty for players resists and melee damage.<br>
<br>
[*]6.05 alter the way pets work in pvp. the level difference between player and pet is completely unfair. change it so when an opponent attempts to cast on your pet, he is met with a resist check as if he cast on the pet master. <br>
<br>
[*]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  BALANCING MELEE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->-<br>
7.01 melee should be given more abilities and skills to make playing more diverse (sort of their own version of spells) -- like a mini aaxp system almost. for example, at level 20 they should be given the option through this system to obstain a gate-like ability (with same restrictions as gate). <br>
<br>
[*]7.02 increase the amount of hate taunt adds.<br>
