<br>
Add casting Foci to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> improve</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> potency of spells, make it easier to cast the spells (less fizzles, perhaps. less mana certainly), give the spells a bonus to hit (harder to resist finely channeled magic as opposed to crudly done), I don't know about a minimum damage since in lots of cases spells smack mobs for max anyways (watch a melee hit for max most of their time. Hah.) Only on uber high end mobs will they hit for nothing, if.. your level isn't anywhere near the creature. Solution to that is to get levels, get inside melee range, and make sure it's been tashed, sundered, malo'd, and everything else you can think of to strip it of protections.<br>
<br>
For pets, these Foci can also be used to help make pets better, to channel them out into a stronger state. Note: We HAVE Foci already for this, BUT we just can't get to them anymore. I doubt we ever could. As it is, the Earth Staff is not thought of as a Focus item, but rather, an Epic Quest piece, and that's primarily why people want it.<br>
<br>
My thoughts on class balancing:<br>
<br>
Casting:<br>
-Perhaps add Spell casting Foci to improve damage/to hit values of spells (this can be taken care of via Arch Alt Advancement skills mostly)<br>
<br>
Pets:<br>
-Add Mage-specific Pet Foci into the game that add a single skill (flurry, rampage, enrage, etc) to the pet, or improve pet damage overall.<br>
-Make pet level comparable to their summoners level. Nothign worse than watching your max 58 hitting pet.. being.. unable to hit anything worth killing because of the massive level difference. (Note: This does not say much for improving pet damage caps, only level-based calculations)<br>
-Improve pathing, Make pets Indifferent. This indiff thing people whine over just means that one can't leave a pet by a KoS mob and get xps while you sleep. It will not mean that the pet will not come to your defense if you get attacked (sheesh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
-Add a spell for binding your pet to you. Lower Valient Companion's level. Nothing worse than being on a raid and.. not being able to use your pet for fear of it being Translocated or Feared away. Binding your pet to you would basically 'intercept' any teleportation attempts on your pet and bring it back to you, with a stun time, perhaps (pet shaken after being trapped between 2 wrenching magics). Valient Companion, people are STILL not used to this spell being available, and since most can't use it anyways unless you're 59, much of your time raiding is without your pet because of fearing mobs.<br>
<br>
I didn't get much of a chance to read the rest, so I'll stop there. For Magicians, our problem is with our pets and the lack of usefullness in big situations. Understand (as I learned recently) that us magicians have a KEEN advantage over other pet classes. Tailoring our pet to the kind of AoE the mob uses. Our pets are highly resistant (should be immune) or immune (fire only) to most kinds of magic (fire, cold, poison, disease). The air pet also seems quite resistant to magic as well (not sure how that works out), just not anywhere near immune. If your pet isn't hit by AoE spells, then it's simply academic. Pet == added damage. Our class does need work, but not necessarily some of the drastic changes proposed. <p>Rhasin Firestorm<BR>
Conjurer of the 55th Season<BR>
