<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
its like a pendulum, in some ways.<br>
<br>
melees have such great ability to scale, because they are almost entirely dependant upon their gear. this means they cannot fight naked very well, but can usually fight better than casters when equiped.<br>
<br>
casters have such a poor ability to scale, because we are almost entirely dependant upon spells and only partially on gear. this means we can fight naked very well, but will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   never</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be as powerful as a well equiped melee.<br>
<br>
this system is weak and biased against casters. <br>
if we ever want equality -- we must become just that, equal. casters must become gear dependant just like melees. one aspect of gear dependancy is an increase in power when equiped. another aspect of gear dependancy is a decrease in power when naked.<br>
<br>
imo, a very fair trade off, dont you think?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
Easier epic: This is a load of horse-@#%$...A big big stinking pile of it. (READ: I WILL NEVER GET MY EPIC) and I'll be DAMNED if any of the people who already have it, are going to get screwed over by people like ME (level 51) who want their epic, but will never get it. Not fair to them, and generally stupid.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
easy, fella. you seem pretty hostile over nothing.<br>
<br>
you have a very selfish outlook towards this issue imo. i dont think mages from here on out should suffer, just because a handful of epic mages had to. <br>
mages need a collective 50+ damage upgrade. making the epic as available as the rage bringer, or celestial fists is a great way to do that.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
Awarded spells: Why should we get our main offensive capabilities (spells) be handed to us at a certain level. Are wurmslayers and lammies handed to melee classes at a certain level? No...I don't need to say much more.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
you dont seem to understand, the whole intent of my idea is to switch casters from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   spell dependant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   gear dependant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <br>
<br>
therefore, spells should just be given out, like melee discs/abilities are... free of charge.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
So in conclusion...You plan to put us on a level playing field, by giving us a WEAKER epic? This is very interesting...If anything, it needs to be BOOSTED MORE, to put us on par with all the velious weapons we DONT get.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
again, if you actually read what i said instead of flamming for no reason, you would have saw that i asked for a post epic pet. a kunark weapon should <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be the most powerful thing we have.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
I am growing very agitated at your belligerent, very narrow views on the world of the magician...Completely shooting down anyone who says anything to contradict you. I'd like to be the first one to respectfully tell you: Stop suggesting...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
most people here are agreeing with my propose to switch mages from spell dependant to gear dependant, since they agree with me: my proposition adds a level of scalability and flexibility to the class spell-dependancy can never provide.<br>
<br>
and, if anyone here was belligerent and narrow, it was you. disagreeing with someone really doesnt give you the right to flame them, and turn a peaceful thread about class balance into a flame war.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
You are very much the minority now with your views, moreso than you have been in the past. You make no friends by suggesting we need to item juggle, and hunt just to cast our god damn spells...And on top of that, I feel it very unnecessary to WEAKEN the most powerful weapon mages have.<br>
<br>
If you agree we are already underpowered, why would you weaken the most powerful weapon?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
in the past, i said the mage epic should be nerfed. the reason i said this, was because by nerfing the ds verant probably wouldnt be as abject to making it as available to 50+ mages, like the rogue and monk epics are.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   but no where in this document do i say the epic should be nerfed.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> i simply say, the epic should be made more available. doing this would be a collective post 50 damage <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   upgrade</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, not a nerf.<br>
<br>
also, keep in mind i advocated the inclusion of post epic pets in ntov/st type zones, just as melees have post epic weapons. so, theoretically even if the epic were to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   very slightly weakened</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, it wouldnt be weakening the most powerful weapon mages have due to the fact more powerful weapons would exist.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
Why the HELL would you nerf unfocused pets? I can see no LOGICAL reason (And above all, not YOUR logic) to support this...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
to make pets dependant upon gear, introducing a level of scalability and flexibility currently not in the game.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
Hey, maybe I'm talking out of my ass...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
you went into flame mode without bothering to understand my ideas, so id say you are.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
But I grow weary at your persistence to weaken our pets, and making a simple task such as spell casting...Require hunting for weapons, and un/equipping them...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
its a necessary step if casters ever want to become equal with melees. you cannot have that level of scalability, without becomming gear dependant.<br>
<br>
you are going to have to take the good (scalability, great damage output), with the minor bad (slightly more difficult crs).<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
By contradicting the majority of the opinions I see here (which might I add are all constructive), you only further prove that you simply posted this to watch yourself type, and to make yourself alltogether feel important...<br>
<br>
You aren't taking constructive criticism, even though you may love arguing with me otherwise.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
most of the posters who disagreed with me, didnt seem to understand the full intent of my post (such as yourself).<br>
<br>
i contradict them, only to try to make them understand <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   why equping focuses would need to become manditory</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. its called a friendly debate.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
I don't apologize for my bluntness...<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
probably because your main intent was to troll. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330" target="new"><b>Noonie Violetskies</b>, 55 High Elven Conjurer</a> <br><b>Aylliah Ravenlure</b>, 32 Erudite Enchantress<br> Morell Thule server.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 1/13/02 6:18:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unoonievioletskies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/02 6:24:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: what i think needs to be done to fix mages...discuss.</span><hr size=1> i would like to thank most of you for keeping this thread friendly, even when you disagree with my ideas.<br>
<br>
some people are biased against me, and automatically go into flame mode whenever i post anything... that hasnt happened (except for one exception) in this thread, and id just like to thank you for keeping it civil. i hope the thread stays that way. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330" target="new"><b>Noonie Violetskies</b>, 55 High Elven Conjurer</a> <br><b>Aylliah Ravenlure</b>, 32 Erudite Enchantress<br> Morell Thule server.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333333>(1/13/02 7:31:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: what i think needs to be done to fix mages...discuss.</span><hr size=1> I understand what you're trying to do, Noonie, but understand I do NOT want gear dependancy. I don't mind scalability upwards, and in some situations, without Foci I'm not doing my proper damage. HOWEVER, I've played my magician to the 55th level with the restrictions and godawful prices we have to pay for some spells. You want to add to that, godawful prices for gear as well. I'm sorry, I don't think many mages are going to go for that JUST to do any sort of damage period. If you think this is going to go well for Wizards or similar (unless you wanted this foci idea mage only.. which wouldn't fly well totally anyway), I doubt that they're going to like it much either.<br>
<br>
Don't you think with the ammount of nerfing that's been done to the Magician class, amungst the meager fixing that's been done, and nerfing to other caster classes (Necros, specifically), I think we're all a little tired of being nerfed, made into nothing more than paperweights, if that. You kind of missed my point that already, casters are gear dependant, just not for direct damage. We don't need weapons, we don't need armor class, necessarily. We need added resistances, we need items to increase our mana pool. We need foci to improve our damage, but why must we take total dependance for any damage what so ever? Just because we have to take some bad with some good? Don't you think the bad we have already (pathing, slow spells baseline, poor damage baseline, poor resists vs higher level mobs, poor pet performance vs higher level mobs) is enough? What else bad do warriors have to deal with if they don't have Uber weapon X? Umm.. just.. damage, right? They still get decent AC without gear, way higher than ours. They.. can't aborb as much damage? Well, yes, I suppose, but even still, HP and AC buffs do quite a bit.<br>
<br>
I'm probably just talking out my rear on what a warrior's deficiency is, but right now, it seems as though they're not very deficiant, and while they need their gear to do any sort of damage (and need to keep upgrading their gear), they don't also incur added costs of spells (sometimes, upwards of 10k if you're really unlucky) and even just finding the stupid spells (Burnout 4, Muzzle of Mardu, Pouch of Quellious, amungst others) is a pain in the rear. As it is right now, finding decent weaponry for Magicians sucks horribly. I know we don't melee much, but for as rare as the Burnt Wood Staff is, and from where it drops, it aught to have something better than Cinder bolt on it, and it aught to be at least a decent 2hb weapon. Some added stats wouldn't be bad. That's just based on the rarity of it.<br>
<br>
Here are some other ideas that might be worthwhile to investigate to make Mages gear dependant:<br>
<br>
-Rare weaponry/items with Lure-based spells on them. Slow casting, but hey, we can at least do damage to lure or highly resistant mobs.<br>
<br>
-Make Pet Foci that we can actually achieve through quests, somewhat ardiously, perhaps, but at least we can achieve them without having to reach the stupid 7th island in Sky. I'd like to see how many mages actually are able to get their Post-50 Foci, and have used them instead of aquired them for the epic only, or ignored getting them (a la Air staff)<br>
<br>
-Make Pet Foci that add special abilities (secondary slot only, can only grant pet a single special ability). Perhaps random (yet not often) flurry attacks, perhaps the ability to rampage, perhaps improve their own skills (reposte, bash, kick), perhaps no special abilities but improve their damage cap a bit.<br>
<br>
-Make channels that we can use/wear. A medallion that we can funnel magic through to boost damage output, gloves that improve casting time.<br>
<br>
I don't think anyone minds needing specialized equipment, BUT crippling us to the point of a level 1 character if we're equipmentless and without a focus to cast spells.. I.. just do not like that what so ever. I figure at higher levels, fighting nastier creatures, we'll become dependant enough on these foci/weapons that without them, we probably wouldn't be asked along. <br>
<br>
And frankly, I could care less what DAoC does about the matter, whomever mentioned it. Everquest isn't DAoC, and I'd rather it not become DAoC. If I want that game, I'll go play it. <p>Rhasin Firestorm<BR>
Conjurer of the 55th Season<BR>
Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=22.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=22.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=22.topic&start=61&stop=76>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=22.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=22.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option valu